reviews.review_text: Heartland Dead This rec has Jerry more upfront centered but is missing the Phil thump. So your trading one for the other but you can still pull some bass out of it w the right software. A good show but still in need of a soundboard to seperate all the other musicians. I'm not surprised by the thousands of arrests made by Hoffman Estates being an uppity outlying Chicago suburb that can't handle anything that looks different then the status quo and the Regan era. Sugaree really smokes w the Jerr Bear flutter in full swing. I wonder if sbds do exist. We have the JGB Popular Creek shows but these never surfaced and when someone said what a few yrs difference can make w the Dead how right you are.
